label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 unmodified form

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that has not been subjected to any co- or post-translational residue modification or peptide bond cleavage.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Ser residue equivalent to Ser-15 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P04637-1. Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Ser-15, MOD:00046.

label.value: cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated 2

value.value: A cellular tumor antigen p53 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at residues equivalent to Ser-15/Ser-46 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P04637-1. Example: UniProtKB:P04637-1, Ser-15/Ser-46, MOD:00046.
A protein that is a translation product of the human MTOR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

An ezrin isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at either the C-terminal Thr (Thr-567 in human), through kinases such as Rho-kinase, or the N-terminal tyrosine residue (Tyr-354 in human). Example: UniProtKB:P15311-1, Tyr-354, MOD:00048|Thr-567, MOD:00047.

label.value: mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase kinase 4

value.value: A protein that is a translation product of the human MAP4K4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase kinase 4 isoform 1

value.value: A mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase kinase 4 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P97820-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human KIF11 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The canonical sequence contains one copy of the Kinesin motor domain (Pfam:PF00225).

A kinesin-like protein KIF11 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P52732-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: kinesin-like protein KIF11 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: A kinesin-like protein KIF11 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.
A kinesin-like protein KIF11 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs by the action of CDK1 during mitosis. Example: UniProtKB:P52732-1, Thr-926, MOD:00047.
A radixin isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

A radixin isoform 1 phosphorylated form that has been activated though Thr phosphorylation by mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase kinase 4 (Nik). Example: UniProtKB:P26044-1, Thr-564, MOD:00047.
A protein that is a translation product of the human TMPRSS9 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A transmembrane protease serine 9 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q7Z410-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A transmembrane protease serine 9 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q0X0F1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A transmembrane protease serine 9 isoform 3 that has been activated by trypsin proteolytic cleavage.

A protein that is a member of the conventional phorbol ester (and diacylglycerol) receptor/protein kinase class. The canonical protein sequence has a core domain architecture consisting of two copies of the Phorbol esters/diacylglycerol binding domain (C1 domain) (Pfam:PF00130), followed by a C2 domain (Pfam:PF00168), a Protein kinase domain (Pfam:PF00069) and a Protein kinase C terminal domain (Pfam:PF00433).
A conventional protein kinase C that is a translation product of the human PRKCA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A conventional protein kinase C that is a translation product of the human PRKCB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A conventional protein kinase C that is a translation product of the human PRKCG gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3 isoform CD3 zeta phosphorylated form

value.value: A T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3 isoform CD3 zeta that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3 isoform CD3 zeta phosphorylated 1

value.value: A T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3 isoform CD3 zeta phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Tyr residues of the tyrosine-based activation motifs (TAMs, also known as Reth motifs), a 15-16 amino acid module containing two tyrosine residues.
A protein that is a translation product of the human SYK or ZAP70 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.
A SYK/ZAP-70 family tyrosine-protein kinase that is a translation product of the human ZAP70 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A SYK/ZAP-70 family tyrosine-protein kinase that is a translation product of the human SYK gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A tyrosine-protein kinase ZAP-70 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P43403-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: tyrosine-protein kinase ZAP-70 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: A tyrosine-protein kinase ZAP-70 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

A tyrosine-protein kinase ZAP-70 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs on several tyrosine residues through autophosphorylation and transphosphorylation by the Src family tyrosine kinase Lck, following TCR engagement. Tyrosine phosphorylation correlates with increased Zap-70 kinase activity and downstream signaling events. It has been shown that Tyr-319 in the human sequence is required for the positive regulation of ZAP-70 function.

A CD4 molecule that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P01730-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A CD4 molecule isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.
A CD4 molecule isoform 1 phosphorylated form that is phosphorylated on Tyr residues yielding the active form.

label.value: signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 isoform 1

value.value: A signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P42224-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: A signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Tyr residue within the conserved GYI sequence following the SH2 domain. Example: UniProtKB:P42224-1, Tyr-701, MOD:00048.

label.value: signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 isoform 2

value.value: A signal transducer and activator of transcription 1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P42224-2 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A neuropilin-1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:O14786-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A neuropilin-1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:O14786-2 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: neuropilin-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed glycosylated form

value.value: A neuropilin-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been post-translationally modified to include a glycosylated residue.

label.value: neuropilin-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed O-glycosylated 1

value.value: A neuropilin-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed glycosylated form that has a heparan sulfate moiety on a Ser residue located in the region between the F5/8 type C domain (Pfam:PF00754) and the MAM domain (Pfam:PF00629). Example: UniProtKB:O14786-1, 22-923, Ser-612, MOD:00215.

label.value: neuropilin-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed O-glycosylated 2

value.value: A neuropilin-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed glycosylated form that has a chondroitin sulfate moiety on a Ser residue located in the region between the F5/8 type C domain (Pfam:PF00754) and the MAM domain (Pfam:PF00629). Example: UniProtKB:O14786-1, 22-923, Ser-612, MOD:00213.

label.value: Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: A Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

label.value: Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at two Ser residues which are the major sites of phosphorylation by PKA and AKT signaling. The sites are the indicated serines within the RxRxxSxP motifs. Phosphorylation on these residues favors binding to 14-3-3 proteins. Example: UniProtKB:Q61337-1, Ser-112/Ser-136, MOD:00046.

label.value: Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated 2

value.value: A Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the indicated Ser residues within each of two RxRxxSxP motifs, and within the RRxS motif located in the BH3 domain. Example: UniProtKB:Q61337-1, Ser-112/Ser-136/Ser-155, MOD:00046.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: The RRxS motif site is the major PKA phosphorylation site. Phosphorylation on these residues favors binding to 14-3-3 proteins.

label.value: Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated 3

value.value: A Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs upon activation of the MAPK pathway. Phosphorylation on this residue favors binding to 14-3-3 proteins. Example: UniProtKB:Q61337-1, Ser-112, MOD:00046.

label.value: apoptosis regulator Bcl-2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: An apoptosis regulator Bcl-2 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.
An apoptosis regulator Bcl-2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs by the action of PKC. Example: UniProtKB:P10417-1, Ser-70, MOD:00046.
A protein that is a translation product of the human CDKN1B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor 1B that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P46527-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
